  "doc_id": "26169",
  "text": "In adults with ID, from a community and out-patient sample in Canada, 34% reported that \"life was not worth living\" sometimes, 23% were thinking about killing themselves and 11% reported that they had attempted to kill themselves in the past [CITATION_1] , while an out-patient psychiatric sample from the US [CITATION_2] reported a finding of 6%. It seems that suicidal behavior is common in persons with mild-moderate ID, while extremely rare in persons with severe-profound ID [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
